  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Colorectal cancer is a common malignancy in Viet Nam. Laparoscopic surgery becomes a standard
      treatment in many centers. Today, robotic surgery is a new option for treating colorectal
      cancer with some advantages such as magnified 3D view, precise movements.

      Answer on safety and feasibility of robotic surgery for colorectal cancer are not available
      in Viet Nam. Therefore, the investigators conducted a study &quot; Robotic versus Laparoscopic
      Approach for Rectal Cancer Surgery&quot;.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
